clauses.clause:
Departmental subject-matter experts are  responsible for the following when speaking in a work capacity and on the  record for public attribution:


  Identifying themselves by name and position.
  Addressing remarks to areas for which they have  responsibility and expertise.

    Respecting:


      privacy rights;
      security needs;
      matters before the courts;
      government laws, regulations and policies; 
      Cabinet confidences and ministerial  responsibilities; and


          Values and Ethics  Code for the Public Sector

        .
